SIMPLE: speculative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Speculative
<hw>Spec"u*la*tive</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ecr⟧k"⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧*t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>sp⟦eacute⟧culatif</ets>, L.
<ets>speculativus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Given to speculation;
contemplative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mind of man being by nature <qex>speculative</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Involving, or formed by, speculation; ideal;
theoretical; not established by demonstration.</def>
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to vision; also, prying;
inquisitive; curious.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to speculation in land, goods,
shares, etc.; <as>as, a <ex>speculative</ex> dealer or
enterprise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>speculative</qex> merchant exercises no one regular,
established, or well-known branch of business.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Finance)</fld> <def>More risky than typical
investments; not investment grade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Spec"u*la*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Spec"u*la*tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Speculator</ent>⟦br⟧
